47 // The "AddHistoryOutput(" must not be split over multiple lines to ensure proper python parsing
48 // clang-format off
49 void CFlowOutput::AddAnalyzeSurfaceOutput(const CConfig *config){
50 
51  /// DESCRIPTION: Average mass flow
52  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_MASSFLOW", "Avg_Massflow", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total average mass flow on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
53  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Mach number
54  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_MACH", "Avg_Mach", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total average mach number on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
55  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Temperature
56  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_STATIC_TEMPERATURE","Avg_Temp", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total average temperature on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
57  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Pressure
58  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE", "Avg_Press", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total average pressure on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
59  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Density
60  AddHistoryOutput("AVG_DENSITY", "Avg_Density", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total average density on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
61  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Enthalpy
62  AddHistoryOutput("AVG_ENTHALPY", "Avg_Enthalpy", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total average enthalpy on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
63  /// DESCRIPTION: Average velocity in normal direction of the surface
64  AddHistoryOutput("AVG_NORMALVEL", "Avg_NormalVel", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total average normal velocity on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
65  /// DESCRIPTION: Flow uniformity
66  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_UNIFORMITY", "Uniformity", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total flow uniformity on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
67  /// DESCRIPTION: Secondary strength
68  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_SECONDARY", "Secondary_Strength", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total secondary strength on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
69  /// DESCRIPTION: Momentum distortion
70  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION", "Momentum_Distortion", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total momentum distortion on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
71  /// DESCRIPTION: Secondary over uniformity
72  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM","Secondary_Over_Uniformity",ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC,"FLOW_COEFF", "Total secondary over uniformity on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
73  /// DESCRIPTION: Average total temperature
74  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_TOTAL_TEMPERATURE","Avg_TotalTemp", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total average total temperature all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
75  /// DESCRIPTION: Average total pressure
76  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE", "Avg_TotalPress", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total average total pressure on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
77  /// DESCRIPTION: Pressure drop
78  if (config->GetnMarker_Analyze() >= 2) {
79  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP", "Pressure_Drop", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF", "Total pressure drop on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
80  } else if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
81  cout << "\nWARNING: SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP can only be computed for at least 2 surfaces (outlet, inlet, ...)\n" << endl;
82  }
83  if (config->GetKind_Species_Model() == SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT) {
84  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Species
85  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < config->GetnSpecies(); iVar++) {
86  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), "Avg_Species_" + std::to_string(iVar), ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "SPECIES_COEFF", "Total average species " + std::to_string(iVar) + " on all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
87  }
88  /// DESCRIPTION: Species Variance
89  AddHistoryOutput("SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE", "Species_Variance", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "SPECIES_COEFF", "Total species variance, measure for mixing quality. On all markers set in MARKER_ANALYZE", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
90  }
91  /// END_GROUP
92 
93  /// BEGIN_GROUP: AERO_COEFF_SURF, DESCRIPTION: Surface values on non-solid markers.
94  vector<string> Marker_Analyze;
95  for (unsigned short iMarker_Analyze = 0; iMarker_Analyze < config->GetnMarker_Analyze(); iMarker_Analyze++){
96  Marker_Analyze.push_back(config->GetMarker_Analyze_TagBound(iMarker_Analyze));
97  }
98 
99  /// DESCRIPTION: Average mass flow
100  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_MASSFLOW", "Avg_Massflow", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
101  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Mach number
102  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_MACH", "Avg_Mach", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
103  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Temperature
104  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_STATIC_TEMPERATURE","Avg_Temp", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
105  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Pressure
106  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE", "Avg_Press", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
107  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Density
108  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("AVG_DENSITY", "Avg_Density", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
109  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Enthalpy
110  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("AVG_ENTHALPY", "Avg_Enthalpy", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
111  /// DESCRIPTION: Average velocity in normal direction of the surface
112  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("AVG_NORMALVEL", "Avg_NormalVel", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
113  /// DESCRIPTION: Flow uniformity
114  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_UNIFORMITY", "Uniformity", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
115  /// DESCRIPTION: Secondary strength
116  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_SECONDARY", "Secondary_Strength", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
117  /// DESCRIPTION: Momentum distortion
118  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION", "Momentum_Distortion", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
119  /// DESCRIPTION: Secondary over uniformity
120  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM","Secondary_Over_Uniformity",ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC,"FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
121  /// DESCRIPTION: Average total temperature
122  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_TOTAL_TEMPERATURE","Avg_TotalTemp", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
123  /// DESCRIPTION: Average total pressure
124  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE", "Avg_TotalPress", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "FLOW_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
125  if (config->GetKind_Species_Model() == SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT) {
126  /// DESCRIPTION: Average Species
127  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < config->GetnSpecies(); iVar++) {
128  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), "Avg_Species_" + std::to_string(iVar), ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "SPECIES_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
129  }
130  /// DESCRIPTION: Species Variance
131  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE", "Species_Variance", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "SPECIES_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Analyze, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
132  }
133 }
134 // clang-format on
135 
136 void CFlowOutput::SetAnalyzeSurface(const CSolver* const*solver, const CGeometry *geometry, CConfig *config, bool output){
137 
138  unsigned short iDim, iMarker, iMarker_Analyze;
139  unsigned long iVertex, iPoint;
140  su2double Mach = 0.0, Pressure, Temperature = 0.0, TotalPressure = 0.0, TotalTemperature = 0.0,
141  Enthalpy, Velocity[3] = {0.0}, TangVel[3], Vector[3], Velocity2, MassFlow, Density, Area,
142  SoundSpeed, Vn, Vn2, Vtang2, Weight = 1.0;
143 
144  const su2double Gas_Constant = config->GetGas_ConstantND();
145  const su2double Gamma = config->GetGamma();
146  const unsigned short nMarker = config->GetnMarker_All();
147  const unsigned short nDim = geometry->GetnDim();
148  const unsigned short Kind_Average = config->GetKind_Average();
149 
150  const bool compressible = config->GetKind_Regime() == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE;
151  const bool incompressible = config->GetKind_Regime() == ENUM_REGIME::INCOMPRESSIBLE;
152  const bool energy = config->GetEnergy_Equation();
153  const bool streamwisePeriodic = (config->GetKind_Streamwise_Periodic() != ENUM_STREAMWISE_PERIODIC::NONE);
154  const bool species = config->GetKind_Species_Model() == SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT;
155  const auto nSpecies = config->GetnSpecies();
156 
157  const bool axisymmetric = config->GetAxisymmetric();
158  const unsigned short nMarker_Analyze = config->GetnMarker_Analyze();
159 
160  const auto flow_nodes = solver[FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes();
161  const CVariable* species_nodes = species ? solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetNodes() : nullptr;
162 
163  vector<su2double> Surface_MassFlow (nMarker,0.0);
164  vector<su2double> Surface_Mach (nMarker,0.0);
165  vector<su2double> Surface_Temperature (nMarker,0.0);
166  vector<su2double> Surface_Density (nMarker,0.0);
167  vector<su2double> Surface_Enthalpy (nMarker,0.0);
168  vector<su2double> Surface_NormalVelocity (nMarker,0.0);
169  vector<su2double> Surface_StreamVelocity2 (nMarker,0.0);
170  vector<su2double> Surface_TransvVelocity2 (nMarker,0.0);
171  vector<su2double> Surface_Pressure (nMarker,0.0);
172  vector<su2double> Surface_TotalTemperature (nMarker,0.0);
173  vector<su2double> Surface_TotalPressure (nMarker,0.0);
174  vector<su2double> Surface_VelocityIdeal (nMarker,0.0);
175  vector<su2double> Surface_Area (nMarker,0.0);
176  vector<su2double> Surface_MassFlow_Abs (nMarker,0.0);
177  su2activematrix Surface_Species(nMarker, nSpecies);
178  Surface_Species = su2double(0.0);
179 
180  su2double Tot_Surface_MassFlow = 0.0;
181  su2double Tot_Surface_Mach = 0.0;
182  su2double Tot_Surface_Temperature = 0.0;
183  su2double Tot_Surface_Density = 0.0;
184  su2double Tot_Surface_Enthalpy = 0.0;
185  su2double Tot_Surface_NormalVelocity = 0.0;
186  su2double Tot_Surface_StreamVelocity2 = 0.0;
187  su2double Tot_Surface_TransvVelocity2 = 0.0;
188  su2double Tot_Surface_Pressure = 0.0;
189  su2double Tot_Surface_TotalTemperature = 0.0;
190  su2double Tot_Surface_TotalPressure = 0.0;
191  su2double Tot_Momentum_Distortion = 0.0;
192  su2double Tot_SecondOverUniformity = 0.0;
193  vector<su2double> Tot_Surface_Species(nSpecies,0.0);
194 
195  /*--- Compute the numerical fan face Mach number, and the total area of the inflow ---*/
196 
197  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker; iMarker++) {
198 
199  if (config->GetMarker_All_Analyze(iMarker) == YES) {
200 
201  for (iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
202 
203  iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
204 
205  if (geometry->nodes->GetDomain(iPoint)) {
206 
207  geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Vector);
208 
209  const su2double AxiFactor = GetAxiFactor(axisymmetric, *geometry->nodes, iPoint, iMarker);
210 
211  Density = flow_nodes->GetDensity(iPoint);
212  Velocity2 = 0.0; Area = 0.0; MassFlow = 0.0; Vn = 0.0; Vtang2 = 0.0;
213 
214  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
215  Area += (Vector[iDim] * AxiFactor) * (Vector[iDim] * AxiFactor);
216  Velocity[iDim] = flow_nodes->GetVelocity(iPoint,iDim);
217  Velocity2 += Velocity[iDim] * Velocity[iDim];
218  Vn += Velocity[iDim] * Vector[iDim] * AxiFactor;
219  MassFlow += Vector[iDim] * AxiFactor * Density * Velocity[iDim];
220  }
221 
222  Area = sqrt (Area);
223  if (AxiFactor == 0.0) Vn = 0.0; else Vn /= Area;
224  Vn2 = Vn * Vn;
225  Pressure = flow_nodes->GetPressure(iPoint);
226  /*--- Use recovered pressure here as pressure difference between in and outlet is zero otherwise ---*/
227  if(streamwisePeriodic) Pressure = flow_nodes->GetStreamwise_Periodic_RecoveredPressure(iPoint);
228  SoundSpeed = flow_nodes->GetSoundSpeed(iPoint);
229 
230  for (iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
231  TangVel[iDim] = Velocity[iDim] - Vn*Vector[iDim]*AxiFactor/Area;
232  Vtang2 += TangVel[iDim]*TangVel[iDim];
233  }
234 
235  if (incompressible){
236  if (config->GetVariable_Density_Model()) {
237  Mach = sqrt(flow_nodes->GetVelocity2(iPoint))/
238  sqrt(flow_nodes->GetSpecificHeatCp(iPoint)*config->GetPressure_ThermodynamicND()/(flow_nodes->GetSpecificHeatCv(iPoint)*flow_nodes->GetDensity(iPoint)));
239  } else {
240  Mach = sqrt(flow_nodes->GetVelocity2(iPoint))/
241  sqrt(config->GetBulk_Modulus()/(flow_nodes->GetDensity(iPoint)));
242  }
243  Temperature = flow_nodes->GetTemperature(iPoint);
244  Enthalpy = flow_nodes->GetSpecificHeatCp(iPoint)*Temperature;
245  TotalTemperature = Temperature + 0.5*Velocity2/flow_nodes->GetSpecificHeatCp(iPoint);
246  TotalPressure = Pressure + 0.5*Density*Velocity2;
247  }
248  else{
249  Mach = sqrt(Velocity2)/SoundSpeed;
250  Temperature = Pressure / (Gas_Constant * Density);
251  Enthalpy = flow_nodes->GetEnthalpy(iPoint);
252  TotalTemperature = Temperature * (1.0 + Mach * Mach * 0.5 * (Gamma - 1.0));
253  TotalPressure = Pressure * pow( 1.0 + Mach * Mach * 0.5 * (Gamma - 1.0), Gamma / (Gamma - 1.0));
254  }
255 
256  /*--- Compute the mass Surface_MassFlow ---*/
257 
258  Surface_Area[iMarker] += Area;
259  Surface_MassFlow[iMarker] += MassFlow;
260  Surface_MassFlow_Abs[iMarker] += abs(MassFlow);
261 
262  if (Kind_Average == AVERAGE_MASSFLUX) Weight = abs(MassFlow);
263  else if (Kind_Average == AVERAGE_AREA) Weight = abs(Area);
264  else Weight = 1.0;
265 
266  Surface_Mach[iMarker] += Mach*Weight;
267  Surface_Temperature[iMarker] += Temperature*Weight;
268  Surface_Density[iMarker] += Density*Weight;
269  Surface_Enthalpy[iMarker] += Enthalpy*Weight;
270  Surface_NormalVelocity[iMarker] += Vn*Weight;
271  Surface_Pressure[iMarker] += Pressure*Weight;
272  Surface_TotalTemperature[iMarker] += TotalTemperature*Weight;
273  Surface_TotalPressure[iMarker] += TotalPressure*Weight;
274  if (species)
275  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nSpecies; iVar++)
276  Surface_Species(iMarker, iVar) += species_nodes->GetSolution(iPoint, iVar)*Weight;
277 
278  /*--- For now, always used the area to weight the uniformities. ---*/
279 
280  Weight = abs(Area);
281 
282  Surface_StreamVelocity2[iMarker] += Vn2*Weight;
283  Surface_TransvVelocity2[iMarker] += Vtang2*Weight;
284 
285  }
286  }
287  }
288  }
289 
290  /*--- Copy to the appropriate structure ---*/
291 
292  vector<su2double> Surface_MassFlow_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
293  vector<su2double> Surface_Mach_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
294  vector<su2double> Surface_Temperature_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
295  vector<su2double> Surface_Density_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
296  vector<su2double> Surface_Enthalpy_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
297  vector<su2double> Surface_NormalVelocity_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
298  vector<su2double> Surface_StreamVelocity2_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
299  vector<su2double> Surface_TransvVelocity2_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
300  vector<su2double> Surface_Pressure_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
301  vector<su2double> Surface_TotalTemperature_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
302  vector<su2double> Surface_TotalPressure_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
303  vector<su2double> Surface_Area_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
304  vector<su2double> Surface_MassFlow_Abs_Local (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
305  su2activematrix Surface_Species_Local(nMarker_Analyze,nSpecies);
306  Surface_Species_Local = su2double(0.0);
307 
308  vector<su2double> Surface_MassFlow_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
309  vector<su2double> Surface_Mach_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
310  vector<su2double> Surface_Temperature_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
311  vector<su2double> Surface_Density_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
312  vector<su2double> Surface_Enthalpy_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
313  vector<su2double> Surface_NormalVelocity_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
314  vector<su2double> Surface_StreamVelocity2_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
315  vector<su2double> Surface_TransvVelocity2_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
316  vector<su2double> Surface_Pressure_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
317  vector<su2double> Surface_TotalTemperature_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
318  vector<su2double> Surface_TotalPressure_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
319  vector<su2double> Surface_Area_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
320  vector<su2double> Surface_MassFlow_Abs_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
321  su2activematrix Surface_Species_Total(nMarker_Analyze,nSpecies);
322  Surface_Species_Total = su2double(0.0);
323 
324  vector<su2double> Surface_MomentumDistortion_Total (nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
325 
326  /*--- Compute the numerical fan face Mach number, mach number, temperature and the total area ---*/
327 
328  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker; iMarker++) {
329 
330  if (config->GetMarker_All_Analyze(iMarker) == YES) {
331 
332  for (iMarker_Analyze= 0; iMarker_Analyze < nMarker_Analyze; iMarker_Analyze++) {
333 
334  /*--- Add the Surface_MassFlow, and Surface_Area to the particular boundary ---*/
335 
336  if (config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker) == config->GetMarker_Analyze_TagBound(iMarker_Analyze)) {
337  Surface_MassFlow_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_MassFlow[iMarker];
338  Surface_Mach_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_Mach[iMarker];
339  Surface_Temperature_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_Temperature[iMarker];
340  Surface_Density_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_Density[iMarker];
341  Surface_Enthalpy_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_Enthalpy[iMarker];
342  Surface_NormalVelocity_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_NormalVelocity[iMarker];
343  Surface_StreamVelocity2_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_StreamVelocity2[iMarker];
344  Surface_TransvVelocity2_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_TransvVelocity2[iMarker];
345  Surface_Pressure_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_Pressure[iMarker];
346  Surface_TotalTemperature_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_TotalTemperature[iMarker];
347  Surface_TotalPressure_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_TotalPressure[iMarker];
348  Surface_Area_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_Area[iMarker];
349  Surface_MassFlow_Abs_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_MassFlow_Abs[iMarker];
350  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nSpecies; iVar++)
351  Surface_Species_Local(iMarker_Analyze, iVar) += Surface_Species(iMarker, iVar);
352  }
353 
354  }
355 
356  }
357 
358  }
359 
360  auto Allreduce = [](const vector<su2double>& src, vector<su2double>& dst) {
361  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(src.data(), dst.data(), src.size(), MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_SUM, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
362  };
363 
364  auto Allreduce_su2activematrix = [](const su2activematrix& src, su2activematrix& dst) {
365  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(src.data(), dst.data(), src.size(), MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_SUM, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
366  };
367 
368  Allreduce(Surface_MassFlow_Local, Surface_MassFlow_Total);
369  Allreduce(Surface_Mach_Local, Surface_Mach_Total);
370  Allreduce(Surface_Temperature_Local, Surface_Temperature_Total);
371  Allreduce(Surface_Density_Local, Surface_Density_Total);
372  Allreduce(Surface_Enthalpy_Local, Surface_Enthalpy_Total);
373  Allreduce(Surface_NormalVelocity_Local, Surface_NormalVelocity_Total);
374  Allreduce(Surface_StreamVelocity2_Local, Surface_StreamVelocity2_Total);
375  Allreduce(Surface_TransvVelocity2_Local, Surface_TransvVelocity2_Total);
376  Allreduce(Surface_Pressure_Local, Surface_Pressure_Total);
377  Allreduce(Surface_TotalTemperature_Local, Surface_TotalTemperature_Total);
378  Allreduce(Surface_TotalPressure_Local, Surface_TotalPressure_Total);
379  Allreduce(Surface_Area_Local, Surface_Area_Total);
380  Allreduce(Surface_MassFlow_Abs_Local, Surface_MassFlow_Abs_Total);
381  Allreduce_su2activematrix(Surface_Species_Local, Surface_Species_Total);
382 
383  /*--- Compute the value of Surface_Area_Total, and Surface_Pressure_Total, and
384  set the value in the config structure for future use ---*/
385 
386  for (iMarker_Analyze = 0; iMarker_Analyze < nMarker_Analyze; iMarker_Analyze++) {
387 
388  if (Kind_Average == AVERAGE_MASSFLUX) Weight = Surface_MassFlow_Abs_Total[iMarker_Analyze];
389  else if (Kind_Average == AVERAGE_AREA) Weight = abs(Surface_Area_Total[iMarker_Analyze]);
390  else Weight = 1.0;
391 
392  if (Weight != 0.0) {
393  Surface_Mach_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Weight;
394  Surface_Temperature_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Weight;
395  Surface_Density_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Weight;
396  Surface_Enthalpy_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Weight;
397  Surface_NormalVelocity_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Weight;
398  Surface_Pressure_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Weight;
399  Surface_TotalTemperature_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Weight;
400  Surface_TotalPressure_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Weight;
401  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nSpecies; iVar++)
402  Surface_Species_Total(iMarker_Analyze, iVar) /= Weight;
403  }
404  else {
405  Surface_Mach_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
406  Surface_Temperature_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
407  Surface_Density_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
408  Surface_Enthalpy_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
409  Surface_NormalVelocity_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
410  Surface_Pressure_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
411  Surface_TotalTemperature_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
412  Surface_TotalPressure_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
413  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nSpecies; iVar++)
414  Surface_Species_Total(iMarker_Analyze, iVar) = 0.0;
415  }
416 
417  /*--- Compute flow uniformity parameters separately (always area for now). ---*/
418 
419  Area = fabs(Surface_Area_Total[iMarker_Analyze]);
420 
421  /*--- The definitions for Distortion and Uniformity Parameters are taken as defined by Banko, Andrew J., et al. in section 3.2 of
422  https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0142727X16301412 ------*/
423 
424  if (Area != 0.0) {
425  Surface_MomentumDistortion_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = Surface_StreamVelocity2_Total[iMarker_Analyze]/(Surface_NormalVelocity_Total[iMarker_Analyze]*Surface_NormalVelocity_Total[iMarker_Analyze]*Area) - 1.0;
426  Surface_StreamVelocity2_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Area;
427  Surface_TransvVelocity2_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Area;
428  }
429  else {
430  Surface_MomentumDistortion_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
431  Surface_StreamVelocity2_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
432  Surface_TransvVelocity2_Total[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
433  }
434 
435  }
436 
437  for (iMarker_Analyze = 0; iMarker_Analyze < nMarker_Analyze; iMarker_Analyze++) {
438 
439  su2double MassFlow = Surface_MassFlow_Total[iMarker_Analyze] * config->GetDensity_Ref() * config->GetVelocity_Ref();
440  if (us_units) MassFlow *= 32.174;
441  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_MASSFLOW", MassFlow, iMarker_Analyze);
442  Tot_Surface_MassFlow += MassFlow;
443  config->SetSurface_MassFlow(iMarker_Analyze, MassFlow);
444 
445  su2double Mach = Surface_Mach_Total[iMarker_Analyze];
446  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_MACH", Mach, iMarker_Analyze);
447  Tot_Surface_Mach += Mach;
448  config->SetSurface_Mach(iMarker_Analyze, Mach);
449 
450  su2double Temperature = Surface_Temperature_Total[iMarker_Analyze] * config->GetTemperature_Ref();
451  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_STATIC_TEMPERATURE", Temperature, iMarker_Analyze);
452  Tot_Surface_Temperature += Temperature;
453  config->SetSurface_Temperature(iMarker_Analyze, Temperature);
454 
455  su2double Pressure = Surface_Pressure_Total[iMarker_Analyze] * config->GetPressure_Ref();
456  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE", Pressure, iMarker_Analyze);
457  Tot_Surface_Pressure += Pressure;
458  config->SetSurface_Pressure(iMarker_Analyze, Pressure);
459 
460  su2double Density = Surface_Density_Total[iMarker_Analyze] * config->GetDensity_Ref();
461  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("AVG_DENSITY", Density, iMarker_Analyze);
462  Tot_Surface_Density += Density;
463  config->SetSurface_Density(iMarker_Analyze, Density);
464 
465  su2double Enthalpy = Surface_Enthalpy_Total[iMarker_Analyze];
466  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("AVG_ENTHALPY", Enthalpy, iMarker_Analyze);
467  Tot_Surface_Enthalpy += Enthalpy;
468  config->SetSurface_Enthalpy(iMarker_Analyze, Enthalpy);
469 
470  su2double NormalVelocity = Surface_NormalVelocity_Total[iMarker_Analyze] * config->GetVelocity_Ref();
471  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("AVG_NORMALVEL", NormalVelocity, iMarker_Analyze);
472  Tot_Surface_NormalVelocity += NormalVelocity;
473  config->SetSurface_NormalVelocity(iMarker_Analyze, NormalVelocity);
474 
475  su2double Uniformity = sqrt(Surface_StreamVelocity2_Total[iMarker_Analyze]) * config->GetVelocity_Ref();
476  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_UNIFORMITY", Uniformity, iMarker_Analyze);
477  Tot_Surface_StreamVelocity2 += Uniformity;
478  config->SetSurface_Uniformity(iMarker_Analyze, Uniformity);
479 
480  su2double SecondaryStrength = sqrt(Surface_TransvVelocity2_Total[iMarker_Analyze]) * config->GetVelocity_Ref();
481  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_SECONDARY", SecondaryStrength, iMarker_Analyze);
482  Tot_Surface_TransvVelocity2 += SecondaryStrength;
483  config->SetSurface_SecondaryStrength(iMarker_Analyze, SecondaryStrength);
484 
485  su2double MomentumDistortion = Surface_MomentumDistortion_Total[iMarker_Analyze];
486  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION", MomentumDistortion, iMarker_Analyze);
487  Tot_Momentum_Distortion += MomentumDistortion;
488  config->SetSurface_MomentumDistortion(iMarker_Analyze, MomentumDistortion);
489 
490  su2double SecondOverUniform = SecondaryStrength/Uniformity;
491  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM", SecondOverUniform, iMarker_Analyze);
492  Tot_SecondOverUniformity += SecondOverUniform;
493  config->SetSurface_SecondOverUniform(iMarker_Analyze, SecondOverUniform);
494 
495  su2double TotalTemperature = Surface_TotalTemperature_Total[iMarker_Analyze] * config->GetTemperature_Ref();
496  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_TOTAL_TEMPERATURE", TotalTemperature, iMarker_Analyze);
497  Tot_Surface_TotalTemperature += TotalTemperature;
498  config->SetSurface_TotalTemperature(iMarker_Analyze, TotalTemperature);
499 
500  su2double TotalPressure = Surface_TotalPressure_Total[iMarker_Analyze] * config->GetPressure_Ref();
501  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE", TotalPressure, iMarker_Analyze);
502  Tot_Surface_TotalPressure += TotalPressure;
503  config->SetSurface_TotalPressure(iMarker_Analyze, TotalPressure);
504 
505  if (species) {
506  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nSpecies; iVar++) {
507  su2double Species = Surface_Species_Total(iMarker_Analyze, iVar);
508  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), Species, iMarker_Analyze);
509  Tot_Surface_Species[iVar] += Species;
510  if (iVar == 0)
511  config->SetSurface_Species_0(iMarker_Analyze, Species);
512  }
513  }
514  }
515 
516  /*--- Compute the average static pressure drop between two surfaces. Note
517  that this assumes we have two surfaces being analyzed and that the outlet
518  is first followed by the inlet. This is because we may also want to choose
519  outlet values (temperature, uniformity, etc.) for our design problems,
520  which require the outlet to be listed first. This is a simple first version
521  that could be generalized to a different orders/lists/etc. ---*/
522 
523  if (nMarker_Analyze >= 2) {
524  su2double PressureDrop = (Surface_Pressure_Total[1] - Surface_Pressure_Total[0]) * config->GetPressure_Ref();
525  for (iMarker_Analyze = 0; iMarker_Analyze < nMarker_Analyze; iMarker_Analyze++) {
526  config->SetSurface_PressureDrop(iMarker_Analyze, PressureDrop);
527  }
528  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP", PressureDrop);
529  }
530  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_MASSFLOW", Tot_Surface_MassFlow);
531  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_MACH", Tot_Surface_Mach);
532  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_STATIC_TEMPERATURE", Tot_Surface_Temperature);
533  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE", Tot_Surface_Pressure);
534  SetHistoryOutputValue("AVG_DENSITY", Tot_Surface_Density);
535  SetHistoryOutputValue("AVG_ENTHALPY", Tot_Surface_Enthalpy);
536  SetHistoryOutputValue("AVG_NORMALVEL", Tot_Surface_NormalVelocity);
537  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_UNIFORMITY", Tot_Surface_StreamVelocity2);
538  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_SECONDARY", Tot_Surface_TransvVelocity2);
539  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION", Tot_Momentum_Distortion);
540  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM", Tot_SecondOverUniformity);
541  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_TOTAL_TEMPERATURE", Tot_Surface_TotalTemperature);
542  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE", Tot_Surface_TotalPressure);
543  if (species) {
544  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nSpecies; iVar++)
545  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), Tot_Surface_Species[iVar]);
546 
547  SetAnalyzeSurfaceSpeciesVariance(solver, geometry, config, Surface_Species_Total, Surface_MassFlow_Abs_Total,
548  Surface_Area_Total);
549  }
550 
551  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && !config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint() && output) {
552 
553  cout.precision(6);
554  cout.setf(ios::scientific, ios::floatfield);
555  cout << endl << "Computing surface mean values." << endl << endl;
556 
557  for (iMarker_Analyze = 0; iMarker_Analyze < nMarker_Analyze; iMarker_Analyze++) {
558  cout << "Surface "<< config->GetMarker_Analyze_TagBound(iMarker_Analyze) << ":" << endl;
559 
560  if (nDim == 3) { if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "Area (m^2): "; else cout << setw(20) << "Area (ft^2): "; }
561  else { if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "Area (m): "; else cout << setw(20) << "Area (ft): "; }
562 
563  if (si_units) cout << setw(15) << fabs(Surface_Area_Total[iMarker_Analyze]);
564  else if (us_units) cout << setw(15) << fabs(Surface_Area_Total[iMarker_Analyze])*12.0*12.0;
565 
566  cout << endl;
567 
568  su2double MassFlow = config->GetSurface_MassFlow(iMarker_Analyze);
569  if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "Mf (kg/s): " << setw(15) << MassFlow;
570  else if (us_units) cout << setw(20) << "Mf (lbs/s): " << setw(15) << MassFlow;
571 
572  su2double NormalVelocity = config->GetSurface_NormalVelocity(iMarker_Analyze);
573  if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "Vn (m/s): " << setw(15) << NormalVelocity;
574  else if (us_units) cout << setw(20) << "Vn (ft/s): " << setw(15) << NormalVelocity;
575 
576  cout << endl;
577 
578  su2double Uniformity = config->GetSurface_Uniformity(iMarker_Analyze);
579  if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "Uniformity (m/s): " << setw(15) << Uniformity;
580  else if (us_units) cout << setw(20) << "Uniformity (ft/s): " << setw(15) << Uniformity;
581 
582  su2double SecondaryStrength = config->GetSurface_SecondaryStrength(iMarker_Analyze);
583  if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "Secondary (m/s): " << setw(15) << SecondaryStrength;
584  else if (us_units) cout << setw(20) << "Secondary (ft/s): " << setw(15) << SecondaryStrength;
585 
586  cout << endl;
587 
588  su2double MomentumDistortion = config->GetSurface_MomentumDistortion(iMarker_Analyze);
589  cout << setw(20) << "Mom. Distortion: " << setw(15) << MomentumDistortion;
590 
591  su2double SecondOverUniform = config->GetSurface_SecondOverUniform(iMarker_Analyze);
592  cout << setw(20) << "Second/Uniform: " << setw(15) << SecondOverUniform;
593 
594  cout << endl;
595 
596  su2double Pressure = config->GetSurface_Pressure(iMarker_Analyze);
597  if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "P (Pa): " << setw(15) << Pressure;
598  else if (us_units) cout << setw(20) << "P (psf): " << setw(15) << Pressure;
599 
600  su2double TotalPressure = config->GetSurface_TotalPressure(iMarker_Analyze);
601  if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "PT (Pa): " << setw(15) <<TotalPressure;
602  else if (us_units) cout << setw(20) << "PT (psf): " << setw(15) <<TotalPressure;
603 
604  cout << endl;
605 
606  su2double Mach = config->GetSurface_Mach(iMarker_Analyze);
607  cout << setw(20) << "Mach: " << setw(15) << Mach;
608 
609  su2double Density = config->GetSurface_Density(iMarker_Analyze);
610  if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "Rho (kg/m^3): " << setw(15) << Density;
611  else if (us_units) cout << setw(20) << "Rho (lb/ft^3): " << setw(15) << Density*32.174;
612 
613  cout << endl;
614 
615  if (compressible || energy) {
616  su2double Temperature = config->GetSurface_Temperature(iMarker_Analyze);
617  if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "T (K): " << setw(15) << Temperature;
618  else if (us_units) cout << setw(20) << "T (R): " << setw(15) << Temperature;
619 
620  su2double TotalTemperature = config->GetSurface_TotalTemperature(iMarker_Analyze);
621  if (si_units) cout << setw(20) << "TT (K): " << setw(15) << TotalTemperature;
622  else if (us_units) cout << setw(20) << "TT (R): " << setw(15) << TotalTemperature;
623 
624  cout << endl;
625  }
626 
627  }
628  cout.unsetf(ios_base::floatfield);
629 
630  }
631 
632  std::cout << std::resetiosflags(std::cout.flags());
633 }
634 
635 void CFlowOutput::SetAnalyzeSurfaceSpeciesVariance(const CSolver* const*solver, const CGeometry *geometry,
636  CConfig *config, const su2activematrix& Surface_Species_Total,
637  const vector<su2double>& Surface_MassFlow_Abs_Total,
638  const vector<su2double>& Surface_Area_Total) {
639 
640  const unsigned short nMarker = config->GetnMarker_All();
641  const unsigned short Kind_Average = config->GetKind_Average();
642 
643  const bool species = config->GetKind_Species_Model() == SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT;
644  const auto nSpecies = config->GetnSpecies();
645 
646  const bool axisymmetric = config->GetAxisymmetric();
647  const unsigned short nMarker_Analyze = config->GetnMarker_Analyze();
648 
649  const auto flow_nodes = solver[FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes();
650  const CVariable* species_nodes = species ? solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetNodes() : nullptr;
651 
652  /*--- Compute Variance of species on the analyze markers. This is done after the rest as the average species value is
653  * necessary. The variance is computed for all species together and not for each species alone. ---*/
654  vector<su2double> Surface_SpeciesVariance(nMarker,0.0);
655  su2double Tot_Surface_SpeciesVariance = 0.0;
656 
657  /*--- sum += (Yj_i - mu_Yj)^2 * weight_i with i representing the node and j the species. ---*/
658  for (unsigned short iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker; iMarker++) {
659 
660  if (config->GetMarker_All_Analyze(iMarker) == YES) {
661 
662  /*--- Find iMarkerAnalyze to iMarker. As SpeciesAvg is accessed via iMarkerAnalyze. ---*/
663  unsigned short iMarker_Analyze_Stored = std::numeric_limits<unsigned short>::max();
664  for (unsigned short iMarker_Analyze = 0; iMarker_Analyze < nMarker_Analyze; iMarker_Analyze++)
665  if (config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker) == config->GetMarker_Analyze_TagBound(iMarker_Analyze))
666  iMarker_Analyze_Stored = iMarker_Analyze;
667 
668  for (unsigned long iVertex = 0; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; iVertex++) {
669  const auto iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
670 
671  if (geometry->nodes->GetDomain(iPoint)) {
672 
673  const su2double AxiFactor = GetAxiFactor(axisymmetric, *geometry->nodes, iPoint, iMarker);
674 
675  su2double Vector[3];
676  geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal(Vector);
677  const su2double Density = flow_nodes->GetDensity(iPoint);
678  su2double Area = 0.0;
679  su2double MassFlow = 0.0;
680 
681  for (unsigned short iDim = 0; iDim < nDim; iDim++) {
682  Area += (Vector[iDim] * AxiFactor) * (Vector[iDim] * AxiFactor);
683  MassFlow += Vector[iDim] * AxiFactor * Density * flow_nodes->GetVelocity(iPoint,iDim);
684  }
685  Area= sqrt(Area);
686 
687  su2double Weight;
688  if (Kind_Average == AVERAGE_MASSFLUX) Weight = abs(MassFlow);
689  else if (Kind_Average == AVERAGE_AREA) Weight = abs(Area);
690  else Weight = 1.0;
691 
692  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < nSpecies; iVar++)
693  Surface_SpeciesVariance[iMarker] += pow(species_nodes->GetSolution(iPoint, iVar) - Surface_Species_Total(iMarker_Analyze_Stored, iVar), 2) * Weight;
694  }
695  }
696  }
697  }
698 
699  /*--- MPI Communication ---*/
700  vector<su2double> Surface_SpeciesVariance_Local(nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
701  vector<su2double> Surface_SpeciesVariance_Total(nMarker_Analyze,0.0);
702 
703  for (unsigned short iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker; iMarker++) {
704 
705  if (config->GetMarker_All_Analyze(iMarker) == YES) {
706 
707  for (unsigned short iMarker_Analyze= 0; iMarker_Analyze < nMarker_Analyze; iMarker_Analyze++) {
708 
709  /*--- Add the Surface_MassFlow, and Surface_Area to the particular boundary ---*/
710 
711  if (config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker) == config->GetMarker_Analyze_TagBound(iMarker_Analyze)) {
712  Surface_SpeciesVariance_Local[iMarker_Analyze] += Surface_SpeciesVariance[iMarker];
713  }
714  }
715  }
716  }
717 
718  auto Allreduce = [](const vector<su2double>& src, vector<su2double>& dst) {
719  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(src.data(), dst.data(), src.size(), MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_SUM, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
720  };
721  Allreduce(Surface_SpeciesVariance_Local, Surface_SpeciesVariance_Total);
722 
723  /*--- Divide quantity by weight. ---*/
724  for (unsigned short iMarker_Analyze = 0; iMarker_Analyze < nMarker_Analyze; iMarker_Analyze++) {
725 
726  su2double Weight;
727  if (Kind_Average == AVERAGE_MASSFLUX) Weight = Surface_MassFlow_Abs_Total[iMarker_Analyze];
728  else if (Kind_Average == AVERAGE_AREA) Weight = abs(Surface_Area_Total[iMarker_Analyze]);
729  else Weight = 1.0;
730 
731  if (Weight != 0.0) {
732  Surface_SpeciesVariance_Total[iMarker_Analyze] /= Weight;
733  }
734  else {
735  Surface_SpeciesVariance[iMarker_Analyze] = 0.0;
736  }
737  }
738 
739  /*--- Set values on markers ---*/
740  for (unsigned short iMarker_Analyze = 0; iMarker_Analyze < nMarker_Analyze; iMarker_Analyze++) {
741  su2double SpeciesVariance = Surface_SpeciesVariance_Total[iMarker_Analyze];
742  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE", SpeciesVariance, iMarker_Analyze);
743  config->SetSurface_Species_Variance(iMarker_Analyze, SpeciesVariance);
744  Tot_Surface_SpeciesVariance += SpeciesVariance;
745  }
746  SetHistoryOutputValue("SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE", Tot_Surface_SpeciesVariance);
747 }
748 
749 void CFlowOutput::ConvertVariableSymbolsToIndices(const CPrimitiveIndices<unsigned long>& idx, const bool allowSkip,
750  CustomOutput& output) const {
751  const auto nameToIndex = PrimitiveNameToIndexMap(idx);
752 
753  std::stringstream knownVariables;
754  for (const auto& items : nameToIndex) {
755  knownVariables << items.first + '\n';
756  }
757  knownVariables << "TURB[0,1,...]\nRAD[0,1,...]\nSPECIES[0,1,...]\nSCALAR[0,1,...]\n";
758 
759  auto IndexOfVariable = [](const map<std::string, unsigned long>& nameToIndex, const std::string& var) {
760  /*--- Primitives of the flow solver. ---*/
761  const auto flowOffset = FLOW_SOL * CustomOutput::MAX_VARS_PER_SOLVER;
762  const auto it = nameToIndex.find(var);
763  if (it != nameToIndex.end()) return flowOffset + it->second;
764 
765  /*--- Index-based (no name) access to variables of other solvers. ---*/
766  auto GetIndex = [](const std::string& s, int nameLen) {
767  /*--- Extract an int from "name[int]", nameLen is the length of "name". ---*/
768  return std::stoi(std::string(s.begin() + nameLen + 1, s.end() - 1));
769  };
770 
771  if (var.rfind("SPECIES", 0) == 0) return SPECIES_SOL * CustomOutput::MAX_VARS_PER_SOLVER + GetIndex(var, 7);
772  if (var.rfind("SCALAR", 0) == 0) return SPECIES_SOL * CustomOutput::MAX_VARS_PER_SOLVER + GetIndex(var, 6);
773  if (var.rfind("TURB", 0) == 0) return TURB_SOL * CustomOutput::MAX_VARS_PER_SOLVER + GetIndex(var, 4);
774  if (var.rfind("RAD", 0) == 0) return RAD_SOL * CustomOutput::MAX_VARS_PER_SOLVER + GetIndex(var, 3);
775  return CustomOutput::NOT_A_VARIABLE;
776  };
777 
778  output.otherOutputs.clear();
779  output.varIndices.clear();
780  output.varIndices.reserve(output.varSymbols.size());
781 
782  for (const auto& var : output.varSymbols) {
783  output.varIndices.push_back(IndexOfVariable(nameToIndex, var));
784 
785  if (output.type == OperationType::FUNCTION && output.varIndices.back() != CustomOutput::NOT_A_VARIABLE) {
786  SU2_MPI::Error("Custom outputs of type 'Function' cannot reference solver variables.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
787  }
788  /*--- Symbol is a valid solver variable. ---*/
789  if (output.varIndices.back() < CustomOutput::NOT_A_VARIABLE) continue;
790 
791  /*--- An index above NOT_A_VARIABLE is not valid with current solver settings. ---*/
792  if (output.varIndices.back() > CustomOutput::NOT_A_VARIABLE) {
793  SU2_MPI::Error("Inactive solver variable (" + var + ") used in function " + output.name + "\n"
794  "E.g. this may only be a variable of the compressible solver.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
795  }
796 
797  /*--- An index equal to NOT_A_VARIABLE may refer to a history output. ---*/
798  output.varIndices.back() += output.otherOutputs.size();
799  output.otherOutputs.push_back(GetPtrToHistoryOutput(var));
800  if (output.otherOutputs.back() == nullptr) {
801  if (!allowSkip) {
802  SU2_MPI::Error("Invalid history output or solver variable (" + var + ") used in function " + output.name +
803  "\nValid solvers variables:\n" + knownVariables.str(), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
804  } else {
805  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
806  std::cout << "Info: Ignoring function " + output.name + " because it may be used by the primal/adjoint "
807  "solver.\n If the function is ignored twice it is invalid." << std::endl;
808  }
809  output.skip = true;
810  break;
811  }
812  }
813  }
814 }
815 
816 void CFlowOutput::SetCustomOutputs(const CSolver* const* solver, const CGeometry *geometry, const CConfig *config) {
817 
818  const bool adjoint = config->GetDiscrete_Adjoint();
819  const bool axisymmetric = config->GetAxisymmetric();
820  const auto* flowNodes = su2staticcast_p<const CFlowVariable*>(solver[FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes());
821 
822  for (auto& output : customOutputs) {
823  if (output.skip) continue;
824 
825  if (output.varIndices.empty()) {
826  const bool allowSkip = adjoint && (output.type == OperationType::FUNCTION);
827 
828  /*--- Setup indices for the symbols in the expression. ---*/
829  const auto primIdx = CPrimitiveIndices<unsigned long>(config->GetKind_Regime() == ENUM_REGIME::INCOMPRESSIBLE,
830  config->GetNEMOProblem(), nDim, config->GetnSpecies());
831  ConvertVariableSymbolsToIndices(primIdx, allowSkip, output);
832  if (output.skip) continue;
833 
834  /*--- Convert marker names to their index (if any) in this rank. Or probe locations to nearest points. ---*/
835 
836  if (output.type != OperationType::PROBE) {
837  output.markerIndices.clear();
838  for (const auto& marker : output.markers) {
839  for (auto iMarker = 0u; iMarker < config->GetnMarker_All(); ++iMarker) {
840  if (config->GetMarker_All_TagBound(iMarker) == marker) {
841  output.markerIndices.push_back(iMarker);
842  continue;
843  }
844  }
845  }
846  } else {
847  if (output.markers.size() != nDim) {
848  SU2_MPI::Error("Wrong number of coordinates to specify probe " + output.name, CURRENT_FUNCTION);
849  }
850  su2double coord[3] = {};
851  for (auto iDim = 0u; iDim < nDim; ++iDim) coord[iDim] = std::stod(output.markers[iDim]);
852  su2double minDist = std::numeric_limits<su2double>::max();
853  unsigned long minPoint = 0;
854  for (auto iPoint = 0ul; iPoint < geometry->GetnPointDomain(); ++iPoint) {
855  const su2double dist = GeometryToolbox::SquaredDistance(nDim, coord, geometry->nodes->GetCoord(iPoint));
856  if (dist < minDist) {
857  minDist = dist;
858  minPoint = iPoint;
859  }
860  }
861  /*--- Decide which rank owns the probe. ---*/
862  su2double globMinDist;
863  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&minDist, &globMinDist, 1, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MIN, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
864  output.iPoint = fabs(minDist - globMinDist) < EPS ? minPoint : CustomOutput::PROBE_NOT_OWNED;
865  if (output.iPoint != CustomOutput::PROBE_NOT_OWNED) {
866  std::cout << "Probe " << output.name << " is using global point "
867  << geometry->nodes->GetGlobalIndex(output.iPoint)
868  << ", distance from target location is " << sqrt(minDist) << std::endl;
869  }
870  }
871  }
872 
873  if (output.type == OperationType::FUNCTION) {
874  auto Functor = [&](unsigned long i) {
875  /*--- Functions only reference other history outputs. ---*/
876  return *output.otherOutputs[i - CustomOutput::NOT_A_VARIABLE];
877  };
878  SetHistoryOutputValue(output.name, output.Eval(Functor));
879  continue;
880  }
881 
882  /*--- Prepares the functor that maps symbol indices to values at a given point
883  * (see ConvertVariableSymbolsToIndices). ---*/
884 
885  auto MakeFunctor = [&](unsigned long iPoint) {
886  /*--- This returns another lambda that captures iPoint by value. ---*/
887  return [&, iPoint](unsigned long i) {
888  if (i < CustomOutput::NOT_A_VARIABLE) {
889  const auto solIdx = i / CustomOutput::MAX_VARS_PER_SOLVER;
890  const auto varIdx = i % CustomOutput::MAX_VARS_PER_SOLVER;
891  if (solIdx == FLOW_SOL) {
892  return flowNodes->GetPrimitive(iPoint, varIdx);
893  }
894  return solver[solIdx]->GetNodes()->GetSolution(iPoint, varIdx);
895  } else {
896  return *output.otherOutputs[i - CustomOutput::NOT_A_VARIABLE];
897  }
898  };
899  };
900 
901  if (output.type == OperationType::PROBE) {
902  su2double value = std::numeric_limits<su2double>::max();
903  if (output.iPoint != CustomOutput::PROBE_NOT_OWNED) {
904  value = output.Eval(MakeFunctor(output.iPoint));
905  }
906  su2double tmp = value;
907  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(&tmp, &value, 1, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MIN, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
908  SetHistoryOutputValue(output.name, value);
909  continue;
910  }
911 
912  /*--- Surface integral of the expression. ---*/
913 
914  std::array<su2double, 2> integral = {0.0, 0.0};
915 
916  SU2_OMP_PARALLEL {
917  std::array<su2double, 2> local_integral = {0.0, 0.0};
918 
919  for (const auto iMarker : output.markerIndices) {
920 
921  SU2_OMP_FOR_(schedule(static) SU2_NOWAIT)
922  for (auto iVertex = 0ul; iVertex < geometry->nVertex[iMarker]; ++iVertex) {
923  const auto iPoint = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNode();
924 
925  if (!geometry->nodes->GetDomain(iPoint)) continue;
926 
927  const auto* normal = geometry->vertex[iMarker][iVertex]->GetNormal();
928 
929  su2double weight = 1.0;
930  if (output.type == OperationType::MASSFLOW_AVG || output.type == OperationType::MASSFLOW_INT) {
931  weight = flowNodes->GetDensity(iPoint) * flowNodes->GetProjVel(iPoint, normal);
932  } else {
933  weight = GeometryToolbox::Norm(nDim, normal);
934  }
935  weight *= GetAxiFactor(axisymmetric, *geometry->nodes, iPoint, iMarker);
936  local_integral[1] += weight;
937  local_integral[0] += weight * output.Eval(MakeFunctor(iPoint));
938  }
939  END_SU2_OMP_FOR
940  }
941 
942  SU2_OMP_CRITICAL {
943  integral[0] += local_integral[0];
944  integral[1] += local_integral[1];
945  }
946  END_SU2_OMP_CRITICAL
947  }
948  END_SU2_OMP_PARALLEL
949 
950  const auto local = integral;
951  SU2_MPI::Allreduce(local.data(), integral.data(), 2, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_SUM, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
952  if (output.type == OperationType::AREA_AVG || output.type == OperationType::MASSFLOW_AVG) {
953  integral[0] /= integral[1];
954  }
955  SetHistoryOutputValue(output.name, integral[0]);
956  }
957 }

959 // The "AddHistoryOutput(" must not be split over multiple lines to ensure proper python parsing

961 void CFlowOutput::AddHistoryOutputFields_ScalarRMS_RES(const CConfig* config) {
962 
963  switch (TurbModelFamily(config->GetKind_Turb_Model())) {
964  case TURB_FAMILY::SA:
965  /// DESCRIPTION: Root-mean square residual of nu tilde (SA model).
966  AddHistoryOutput("RMS_NU_TILDE", "rms[nu]", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "RMS_RES", "Root-mean square residual of nu tilde (SA model).", HistoryFieldType::RESIDUAL);
967  break;
968 
969  case TURB_FAMILY::KW:
970  /// DESCRIPTION: Root-mean square residual of kinetic energy (SST model).
971  AddHistoryOutput("RMS_TKE", "rms[k]", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "RMS_RES", "Root-mean square residual of kinetic energy (SST model).", HistoryFieldType::RESIDUAL);
972  /// DESCRIPTION: Root-mean square residual of the dissipation (SST model).
973  AddHistoryOutput("RMS_DISSIPATION", "rms[w]", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "RMS_RES", "Root-mean square residual of dissipation (SST model).", HistoryFieldType::RESIDUAL);
974  break;
975 
976  case TURB_FAMILY::NONE: break;
977  }
978  switch (config->GetKind_Trans_Model()) {
979 
980  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM:
981  /// DESCRIPTION: Root-mean square residual of the intermittency (LM model).
982  AddHistoryOutput("RMS_INTERMITTENCY", "rms[LM_1]", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "RMS_RES", "Root-mean square residual of intermittency (LM model).", HistoryFieldType::RESIDUAL);
983  /// DESCRIPTION: Root-mean square residual of the momentum thickness Reynolds number (LM model).
984  AddHistoryOutput("RMS_RE_THETA_T", "rms[LM_2]", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "RMS_RES", "Root-mean square residual of momentum thickness Reynolds number (LM model).", HistoryFieldType::RESIDUAL);
985  break;
986 
987  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::NONE: break;
988  }
989 
990  switch (config->GetKind_Species_Model()) {
991  case SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT: {
992  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < config->GetnSpecies(); iVar++) {
993  AddHistoryOutput("RMS_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), "rms[rho*Y_" + std::to_string(iVar)+"]", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "RMS_RES", "Root-mean square residual of transported species.", HistoryFieldType::RESIDUAL);
994  }
995  break;
996  }
997  case SPECIES_MODEL::FLAMELET: {
998  /*--- Controlling variable transport. ---*/
999  for (auto iCV = 0u; iCV < config->GetNControlVars(); iCV++){
1000  const auto& CV_name = config->GetControllingVariableName(iCV);
1001  AddHistoryOutput("RMS_"+CV_name, "rms["+CV_name+"]",ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "RMS_RES", "Root-mean squared residual of " + CV_name + " controlling variable equation.", HistoryFieldType::RESIDUAL);
1002  }
1003 
1004  /*--- auxiliary species transport ---*/
1005  for (auto i_scalar = 0u; i_scalar < config->GetNUserScalars(); i_scalar++){
1006  const auto& scalar_name = config->GetUserScalarName(i_scalar);
1007  AddHistoryOutput("RMS_"+scalar_name, "rms["+scalar_name+"]", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED , "RMS_RES", "Root-mean squared residual of the "+scalar_name+" mass fraction equation." , HistoryFieldType::RESIDUAL);
1008  }
1009  break;
1010  }
1011  case SPECIES_MODEL::NONE: break;
1012  }
1013 }

1154 void CFlowOutput::LoadHistoryDataScalar(const CConfig* config, const CSolver* const* solver) {
1155 
1156  switch (TurbModelFamily(config->GetKind_Turb_Model())) {
1157  case TURB_FAMILY::SA:
1158  SetHistoryOutputValue("RMS_NU_TILDE", log10(solver[TURB_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(0)));
1159  SetHistoryOutputValue("MAX_NU_TILDE", log10(solver[TURB_SOL]->GetRes_Max(0)));
1160  if (multiZone) {
1161  SetHistoryOutputValue("BGS_NU_TILDE", log10(solver[TURB_SOL]->GetRes_BGS(0)));
1162  }
1163  break;
1164 
1165  case TURB_FAMILY::KW:
1166  SetHistoryOutputValue("RMS_TKE", log10(solver[TURB_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(0)));
1167  SetHistoryOutputValue("RMS_DISSIPATION",log10(solver[TURB_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(1)));
1168  SetHistoryOutputValue("MAX_TKE", log10(solver[TURB_SOL]->GetRes_Max(0)));
1169  SetHistoryOutputValue("MAX_DISSIPATION", log10(solver[TURB_SOL]->GetRes_Max(1)));
1170  if (multiZone) {
1171  SetHistoryOutputValue("BGS_TKE", log10(solver[TURB_SOL]->GetRes_BGS(0)));
1172  SetHistoryOutputValue("BGS_DISSIPATION", log10(solver[TURB_SOL]->GetRes_BGS(1)));
1173  }
1174  break;
1175 
1176  case TURB_FAMILY::NONE: break;
1177  }
1178 
1179  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() != TURB_MODEL::NONE) {
1180  SetHistoryOutputValue("LINSOL_ITER_TURB", solver[TURB_SOL]->GetIterLinSolver());
1181  SetHistoryOutputValue("LINSOL_RESIDUAL_TURB", log10(solver[TURB_SOL]->GetResLinSolver()));
1182  }
1183 
1184  switch (config->GetKind_Trans_Model()) {
1185  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM:
1186  SetHistoryOutputValue("RMS_INTERMITTENCY", log10(solver[TRANS_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(0)));
1187  SetHistoryOutputValue("RMS_RE_THETA_T",log10(solver[TRANS_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(1)));
1188  SetHistoryOutputValue("MAX_INTERMITTENCY", log10(solver[TRANS_SOL]->GetRes_Max(0)));
1189  SetHistoryOutputValue("MAX_RE_THETA_T", log10(solver[TRANS_SOL]->GetRes_Max(1)));
1190  if (multiZone) {
1191  SetHistoryOutputValue("BGS_INTERMITTENCY", log10(solver[TRANS_SOL]->GetRes_BGS(0)));
1192  SetHistoryOutputValue("BGS_RE_THETA_T", log10(solver[TRANS_SOL]->GetRes_BGS(1)));
1193  }
1194  SetHistoryOutputValue("LINSOL_ITER_TRANS", solver[TRANS_SOL]->GetIterLinSolver());
1195  SetHistoryOutputValue("LINSOL_RESIDUAL_TRANS", log10(solver[TRANS_SOL]->GetResLinSolver()));
1196  break;
1197 
1198  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::NONE: break;
1199  }
1200 
1201  switch(config->GetKind_Species_Model()) {
1202  case SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT: {
1203  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < config->GetnSpecies(); iVar++) {
1204  SetHistoryOutputValue("RMS_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(iVar)));
1205  SetHistoryOutputValue("MAX_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetRes_Max(iVar)));
1206  if (multiZone) {
1207  SetHistoryOutputValue("BGS_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetRes_BGS(iVar)));
1208  }
1209  }
1210  SetHistoryOutputValue("LINSOL_ITER_SPECIES", solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetIterLinSolver());
1211  SetHistoryOutputValue("LINSOL_RESIDUAL_SPECIES", log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetResLinSolver()));
1212  break;
1213  }
1214 
1215  case SPECIES_MODEL::FLAMELET: {
1216  /*--- Controlling variable transport. ---*/
1217  for (auto iCV=0u; iCV < config->GetNControlVars(); iCV++){
1218  const auto& cv_name = config->GetControllingVariableName(iCV);
1219  SetHistoryOutputValue("RMS_" + cv_name, log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(iCV)));
1220  SetHistoryOutputValue("MAX_" + cv_name, log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetRes_Max(iCV)));
1221  if (multiZone) {
1222  SetHistoryOutputValue("BGS_" + cv_name, log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetRes_BGS(iCV)));
1223  }
1224  }
1225  /*--- auxiliary species transport ---*/
1226  for (unsigned short iReactant=0; iReactant<config->GetNUserScalars(); iReactant++){
1227  const auto& species_name = config->GetUserScalarName(iReactant);
1228  SetHistoryOutputValue("RMS_" + species_name, log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetRes_RMS(config->GetNControlVars() + iReactant)));
1229  SetHistoryOutputValue("MAX_" + species_name, log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetRes_Max(config->GetNControlVars() + iReactant)));
1230  if (multiZone) {
1231  SetHistoryOutputValue("BGS_" + species_name, log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetRes_BGS(config->GetNControlVars() + iReactant)));
1232  }
1233  }
1234 
1235  SetHistoryOutputValue("LINSOL_ITER_FLAMELET", solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetIterLinSolver());
1236  SetHistoryOutputValue("LINSOL_RESIDUAL_FLAMELET", log10(solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetResLinSolver()));
1237  break;
1238  }
1239 
1240  case SPECIES_MODEL::NONE: break;
1241  }
1242 }

1244 void CFlowOutput::SetVolumeOutputFieldsScalarSolution(const CConfig* config){
1245  /*--- Only place outputs of the "SOLUTION" group here. ---*/
1246 
1247  switch (TurbModelFamily(config->GetKind_Turb_Model())) {
1248  case TURB_FAMILY::SA:
1249  AddVolumeOutput("NU_TILDE", "Nu_Tilde", "SOLUTION", "Spalart-Allmaras variable");
1250  break;
1251 
1252  case TURB_FAMILY::KW:
1253  AddVolumeOutput("TKE", "Turb_Kin_Energy", "SOLUTION", "Turbulent kinetic energy");
1254  AddVolumeOutput("DISSIPATION", "Omega", "SOLUTION", "Rate of dissipation");
1255  break;
1256 
1257  case TURB_FAMILY::NONE:
1258  break;
1259  }
1260 
1261  switch (config->GetKind_Trans_Model()) {
1262  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM:
1263  AddVolumeOutput("INTERMITTENCY", "LM_gamma", "SOLUTION", "LM intermittency");
1264  AddVolumeOutput("RE_THETA_T", "LM_Re_t", "SOLUTION", "LM RE_THETA_T");
1265  break;
1266 
1267  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::NONE:
1268  break;
1269  }
1270 
1271  switch (config->GetKind_Species_Model()) {
1272  case SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT:
1273  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < config->GetnSpecies(); iVar++){
1274  AddVolumeOutput("SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), "Species_" + std::to_string(iVar), "SOLUTION", "Species_" + std::to_string(iVar) + " mass fraction");
1275  }
1276  break;
1277  case SPECIES_MODEL::FLAMELET:
1278  /*--- Controlling variables. ---*/
1279  for (auto iCV=0u; iCV<config->GetNControlVars(); iCV++) {
1280  const auto& cv_name = config->GetControllingVariableName(iCV);
1281  AddVolumeOutput(cv_name, cv_name, "SOLUTION", cv_name + " solution.");
1282  }
1283  /*--- auxiliary species ---*/
1284  for (auto iReactant=0u; iReactant<config->GetNUserScalars(); iReactant++) {
1285  const auto& species_name = config->GetUserScalarName(iReactant);
1286  AddVolumeOutput(species_name, species_name, "SOLUTION", species_name + "Mass fraction solution");
1287  }
1288 
1289  break;
1290  case SPECIES_MODEL::NONE:
1291  break;
1292  }
1293 }

1295 void CFlowOutput::SetVolumeOutputFieldsScalarResidual(const CConfig* config) {
1296  /*--- Only place outputs of the "RESIDUAL" group here. ---*/
1297 
1298  switch (TurbModelFamily(config->GetKind_Turb_Model())){
1299  case TURB_FAMILY::SA:
1300  AddVolumeOutput("RES_NU_TILDE", "Residual_Nu_Tilde", "RESIDUAL", "Residual of the Spalart-Allmaras variable");
1301  break;
1302 
1303  case TURB_FAMILY::KW:
1304  AddVolumeOutput("RES_TKE", "Residual_TKE", "RESIDUAL", "Residual of turbulent kinetic energy");
1305  AddVolumeOutput("RES_DISSIPATION", "Residual_Omega", "RESIDUAL", "Residual of the rate of dissipation");
1306  break;
1307 
1308  case TURB_FAMILY::NONE:
1309  break;
1310  }
1311 
1312  switch (config->GetKind_Species_Model()) {
1313  case SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT:
1314  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < config->GetnSpecies(); iVar++){
1315  AddVolumeOutput("RES_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), "Residual_Species_" + std::to_string(iVar), "RESIDUAL", "Residual of the transported species " + std::to_string(iVar));
1316  }
1317  break;
1318  case SPECIES_MODEL::FLAMELET:
1319  /*--- Residuals for controlling variable transport equations. ---*/
1320  for (auto iCV=0u; iCV<config->GetNControlVars(); iCV++) {
1321  const auto& cv_name = config->GetControllingVariableName(iCV);
1322  AddVolumeOutput("RES_"+cv_name, "Residual_"+cv_name, "RESIDUAL", "Residual of " + cv_name + " controlling variable.");
1323  }
1324  /*--- residuals for auxiliary species transport equations ---*/
1325  for (unsigned short iReactant=0; iReactant<config->GetNUserScalars(); iReactant++){
1326  const auto& species_name = config->GetUserScalarName(iReactant);
1327  AddVolumeOutput("RES_" + species_name, "Residual_" + species_name, "RESIDUAL", "Residual of the " + species_name + " equation");
1328  }
1329  break;
1330  case SPECIES_MODEL::NONE:
1331  break;
1332  }
1333 
1334  switch (config->GetKind_Trans_Model()) {
1335  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM:
1336  AddVolumeOutput("RES_INTERMITTENCY", "Residual_LM_intermittency", "RESIDUAL", "Residual of LM intermittency");
1337  AddVolumeOutput("RES_RE_THETA_T", "Residual_LM_RE_THETA_T", "RESIDUAL", "Residual of LM RE_THETA_T");
1338  break;
1339 
1340  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::NONE:
1341  break;
1342  }
1343 }

1460 void CFlowOutput::SetVolumeOutputFieldsScalarMisc(const CConfig* config) {
1461  /*--- Only place outputs of the group for scalar transport here that do not fit in other categories. ---*/
1462 
1463  if (config->GetSAParsedOptions().bc) {
1464  AddVolumeOutput("INTERMITTENCY", "gamma_BC", "INTERMITTENCY", "Intermittency");
1465  }
1466 
1467  // Hybrid RANS-LES
1468  if (config->GetKind_HybridRANSLES() != NO_HYBRIDRANSLES) {
1469  AddVolumeOutput("DES_LENGTHSCALE", "DES_LengthScale", "DDES", "DES length scale value");
1470  AddVolumeOutput("WALL_DISTANCE", "Wall_Distance", "DDES", "Wall distance value");
1471  }
1472 
1473  if (config->GetViscous()) {
1474  if (nDim == 3) {
1475  AddVolumeOutput("VORTICITY_X", "Vorticity_x", "VORTEX_IDENTIFICATION", "x-component of the vorticity vector");
1476  AddVolumeOutput("VORTICITY_Y", "Vorticity_y", "VORTEX_IDENTIFICATION", "y-component of the vorticity vector");
1477  AddVolumeOutput("VORTICITY_Z", "Vorticity_z", "VORTEX_IDENTIFICATION", "z-component of the vorticity vector");
1478  } else {
1479  AddVolumeOutput("VORTICITY", "Vorticity", "VORTEX_IDENTIFICATION", "Value of the vorticity");
1480  }
1481  AddVolumeOutput("Q_CRITERION", "Q_Criterion", "VORTEX_IDENTIFICATION", "Value of the Q-Criterion");
1482  }
1483 
1484  // Timestep info
1485  AddVolumeOutput("DELTA_TIME", "Delta_Time", "TIMESTEP", "Value of the local timestep for the flow variables");
1486  AddVolumeOutput("CFL", "CFL", "TIMESTEP", "Value of the local CFL for the flow variables");
1487  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() != TURB_MODEL::NONE)
1488  {
1489  AddVolumeOutput("TURB_DELTA_TIME", "Turb_Delta_Time", "TIMESTEP", "Value of the local timestep for the turbulence variables");
1490  AddVolumeOutput("TURB_CFL", "Turb_CFL", "TIMESTEP", "Value of the local CFL for the turbulence variables");
1491  }

1494 void CFlowOutput::LoadVolumeDataScalar(const CConfig* config, const CSolver* const* solver, const CGeometry* geometry,
1495  const unsigned long iPoint) {
1496  const auto* turb_solver = solver[TURB_SOL];
1497  const auto* trans_solver = solver[TRANS_SOL];
1498  const auto* Node_Flow = solver[FLOW_SOL]->GetNodes();
1499  const auto* Node_Turb = (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() != TURB_MODEL::NONE) ? turb_solver->GetNodes() : nullptr;
1500  const auto* Node_Trans = (config->GetKind_Trans_Model() != TURB_TRANS_MODEL::NONE) ? trans_solver->GetNodes() : nullptr;
1501  const auto* Node_Geo = geometry->nodes;
1502 
1503  SetVolumeOutputValue("DELTA_TIME", iPoint, Node_Flow->GetDelta_Time(iPoint));
1504  SetVolumeOutputValue("CFL", iPoint, Node_Flow->GetLocalCFL(iPoint));
1505 
1506  if (config->GetViscous()) {
1507  if (nDim == 3){
1508  SetVolumeOutputValue("VORTICITY_X", iPoint, Node_Flow->GetVorticity(iPoint)[0]);
1509  SetVolumeOutputValue("VORTICITY_Y", iPoint, Node_Flow->GetVorticity(iPoint)[1]);
1510  SetVolumeOutputValue("VORTICITY_Z", iPoint, Node_Flow->GetVorticity(iPoint)[2]);
1511  } else {
1512  SetVolumeOutputValue("VORTICITY", iPoint, Node_Flow->GetVorticity(iPoint)[2]);
1513  }
1514  SetVolumeOutputValue("Q_CRITERION", iPoint, GetQCriterion(Node_Flow->GetVelocityGradient(iPoint)));
1515  }
1516 
1517  const bool limiter = (config->GetKind_SlopeLimit_Turb() != LIMITER::NONE);
1518 
1519  switch (TurbModelFamily(config->GetKind_Turb_Model())) {
1520  case TURB_FAMILY::SA:
1521  SetVolumeOutputValue("NU_TILDE", iPoint, Node_Turb->GetSolution(iPoint, 0));
1522  SetVolumeOutputValue("RES_NU_TILDE", iPoint, turb_solver->LinSysRes(iPoint, 0));
1523  if (limiter) {
1524  SetVolumeOutputValue("LIMITER_NU_TILDE", iPoint, Node_Turb->GetLimiter(iPoint, 0));
1525  }
1526  break;
1527 
1528  case TURB_FAMILY::KW:
1529  SetVolumeOutputValue("TKE", iPoint, Node_Turb->GetSolution(iPoint, 0));
1530  SetVolumeOutputValue("DISSIPATION", iPoint, Node_Turb->GetSolution(iPoint, 1));
1531  SetVolumeOutputValue("RES_TKE", iPoint, turb_solver->LinSysRes(iPoint, 0));
1532  SetVolumeOutputValue("RES_DISSIPATION", iPoint, turb_solver->LinSysRes(iPoint, 1));
1533  if (limiter) {
1534  SetVolumeOutputValue("LIMITER_TKE", iPoint, Node_Turb->GetLimiter(iPoint, 0));
1535  SetVolumeOutputValue("LIMITER_DISSIPATION", iPoint, Node_Turb->GetLimiter(iPoint, 1));
1536  }
1537  break;
1538 
1539  case TURB_FAMILY::NONE: break;
1540  }
1541 
1542  /*--- If we got here a turbulence model is being used, therefore there is eddy viscosity. ---*/
1543  if (config->GetKind_Turb_Model() != TURB_MODEL::NONE) {
1544  SetVolumeOutputValue("EDDY_VISCOSITY", iPoint, Node_Flow->GetEddyViscosity(iPoint));
1545  SetVolumeOutputValue("TURB_DELTA_TIME", iPoint, Node_Turb->GetDelta_Time(iPoint));
1546  SetVolumeOutputValue("TURB_CFL", iPoint, Node_Turb->GetLocalCFL(iPoint));
1547  }
1548 
1549  if (config->GetSAParsedOptions().bc) {
1550  SetVolumeOutputValue("INTERMITTENCY", iPoint, Node_Turb->GetIntermittencyEff(iPoint));
1551  }
1552 
1553  switch (config->GetKind_Trans_Model()) {
1554  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM:
1555  SetVolumeOutputValue("INTERMITTENCY", iPoint, Node_Trans->GetSolution(iPoint, 0));
1556  SetVolumeOutputValue("RE_THETA_T", iPoint, Node_Trans->GetSolution(iPoint, 1));
1557  SetVolumeOutputValue("INTERMITTENCY_SEP", iPoint, Node_Trans->GetIntermittencySep(iPoint));
1558  SetVolumeOutputValue("INTERMITTENCY_EFF", iPoint, Node_Trans->GetIntermittencyEff(iPoint));
1559  SetVolumeOutputValue("TURB_INDEX", iPoint, Node_Turb->GetTurbIndex(iPoint));
1560  SetVolumeOutputValue("RES_INTERMITTENCY", iPoint, trans_solver->LinSysRes(iPoint, 0));
1561  SetVolumeOutputValue("RES_RE_THETA_T", iPoint, trans_solver->LinSysRes(iPoint, 1));
1562  break;
1563 
1564  case TURB_TRANS_MODEL::NONE: break;
1565  }
1566 
1567  if (config->GetKind_HybridRANSLES() != NO_HYBRIDRANSLES) {
1568  SetVolumeOutputValue("DES_LENGTHSCALE", iPoint, Node_Flow->GetDES_LengthScale(iPoint));
1569  SetVolumeOutputValue("WALL_DISTANCE", iPoint, Node_Geo->GetWall_Distance(iPoint));
1570  }
1571 
1572  switch (config->GetKind_Species_Model()) {
1573 
1574  case SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT: {
1575  const auto Node_Species = solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetNodes();
1576  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < config->GetnSpecies(); iVar++) {
1577  SetVolumeOutputValue("SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), iPoint, Node_Species->GetSolution(iPoint, iVar));
1578  SetVolumeOutputValue("RES_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), iPoint, solver[SPECIES_SOL]->LinSysRes(iPoint, iVar));
1579  SetVolumeOutputValue("DIFFUSIVITY_"+ std::to_string(iVar), iPoint, Node_Species->GetDiffusivity(iPoint,iVar));
1580  if (config->GetKind_SlopeLimit_Species() != LIMITER::NONE)
1581  SetVolumeOutputValue("LIMITER_SPECIES_" + std::to_string(iVar), iPoint, Node_Species->GetLimiter(iPoint, iVar));
1582  }
1583  break;
1584  }
1585 
1586  case SPECIES_MODEL::FLAMELET: {
1587  const auto Node_Species = solver[SPECIES_SOL]->GetNodes();
1588 
1589  /*--- Controlling variables transport equations. ---*/
1590  for (auto iCV=0u; iCV < config->GetNControlVars(); iCV++) {
1591  const auto& cv_name = config->GetControllingVariableName(iCV);
1592  SetVolumeOutputValue(cv_name, iPoint, Node_Species->GetSolution(iPoint, iCV));
1593  SetVolumeOutputValue("RES_" + cv_name, iPoint, solver[SPECIES_SOL]->LinSysRes(iPoint, iCV));
1594  const auto& source_name = config->GetControllingVariableSourceName(iCV);
1595  if (source_name.compare("NULL") != 0)
1596  SetVolumeOutputValue("SOURCE_" + cv_name, iPoint, Node_Species->GetScalarSources(iPoint)[iCV]);
1597  }
1598  /*--- auxiliary species transport equations ---*/
1599  for (unsigned short i_scalar=0; i_scalar<config->GetNUserScalars(); i_scalar++) {
1600  const auto& scalar_name = config->GetUserScalarName(i_scalar);
1601  SetVolumeOutputValue(scalar_name, iPoint, Node_Species->GetSolution(iPoint, config->GetNControlVars() + i_scalar));
1602  SetVolumeOutputValue("SOURCE_" + scalar_name, iPoint, Node_Species->GetScalarSources(iPoint)[config->GetNControlVars() + i_scalar]);
1603  SetVolumeOutputValue("RES_" + scalar_name, iPoint, solver[SPECIES_SOL]->LinSysRes(iPoint, config->GetNControlVars() + i_scalar));
1604  }
1605 
1606  if (config->GetKind_SlopeLimit_Species() != LIMITER::NONE) {
1607  /*--- Limiter for controlling variable transport equations. ---*/
1608  for (auto iCV=0u; iCV<config->GetNControlVars(); iCV++) {
1609  const auto& cv_name = config->GetControllingVariableName(iCV);
1610  SetVolumeOutputValue("LIMITER_" + cv_name, iPoint, Node_Species->GetLimiter(iPoint, iCV));
1611  }
1612  /*--- limiter for auxiliary species transport equations ---*/
1613  for (unsigned short i_scalar=0; i_scalar<config->GetNUserScalars(); i_scalar++) {
1614  const auto& scalar_name = config->GetUserScalarName(i_scalar);
1615  SetVolumeOutputValue("LIMITER_" + scalar_name, iPoint, Node_Species->GetLimiter(iPoint, config->GetNControlVars() + i_scalar));
1616  }
1617  }
1618 
1619  /*--- variables that we look up from the LUT ---*/
1620  for (int i_lookup = 0; i_lookup < config->GetNLookups(); ++i_lookup) {
1621  if (config->GetLookupName(i_lookup)!="NULL")
1622  SetVolumeOutputValue(config->GetLookupName(i_lookup), iPoint, Node_Species->GetScalarLookups(iPoint)[i_lookup]);
1623  }
1624 
1625  SetVolumeOutputValue("TABLE_MISSES", iPoint, Node_Species->GetTableMisses(iPoint));
1626 
1627  break;
1628  }
1629  case SPECIES_MODEL::NONE: break;
1630  }
1631 }
1632 
1633 void CFlowOutput::LoadSurfaceData(CConfig *config, CGeometry *geometry, CSolver **solver, unsigned long iPoint, unsigned short iMarker, unsigned long iVertex){
1634 
1635  if (!config->GetViscous_Wall(iMarker)) return;
1636 
1637  const auto heat_sol = (config->GetKind_Regime() == ENUM_REGIME::INCOMPRESSIBLE) &&
1638  config->GetWeakly_Coupled_Heat() ? HEAT_SOL : FLOW_SOL;
1639 
1640  SetVolumeOutputValue("SKIN_FRICTION-X", iPoint, solver[FLOW_SOL]->GetCSkinFriction(iMarker, iVertex, 0));
1641  SetVolumeOutputValue("SKIN_FRICTION-Y", iPoint, solver[FLOW_SOL]->GetCSkinFriction(iMarker, iVertex, 1));
1642  if (nDim == 3)
1643  SetVolumeOutputValue("SKIN_FRICTION-Z", iPoint, solver[FLOW_SOL]->GetCSkinFriction(iMarker, iVertex, 2));
1644  SetVolumeOutputValue("HEAT_FLUX", iPoint, solver[heat_sol]->GetHeatFlux(iMarker, iVertex));
1645  SetVolumeOutputValue("Y_PLUS", iPoint, solver[FLOW_SOL]->GetYPlus(iMarker, iVertex));
1646 }
1647 
1648 void CFlowOutput::AddAerodynamicCoefficients(const CConfig* config) {
1649 
1650  /// BEGIN_GROUP: AERO_COEFF, DESCRIPTION: Sum of the aerodynamic coefficients and forces on all surfaces (markers) set with MARKER_MONITORING.
1651  /// DESCRIPTION: Reference force for aerodynamic coefficients
1652  AddHistoryOutput("REFERENCE_FORCE", "RefForce", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Reference force used to compute aerodynamic coefficients", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1653  /// DESCRIPTION: Drag coefficient
1654  AddHistoryOutput("DRAG", "CD", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Total drag coefficient on all surfaces set with MARKER_MONITORING", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1655  /// DESCRIPTION: Lift coefficient
1656  AddHistoryOutput("LIFT", "CL", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Total lift coefficient on all surfaces set with MARKER_MONITORING", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1657  /// DESCRIPTION: Sideforce coefficient
1658  AddHistoryOutput("SIDEFORCE", "CSF", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Total sideforce coefficient on all surfaces set with MARKER_MONITORING", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1659  /// DESCRIPTION: Moment around the x-axis
1660  AddHistoryOutput("MOMENT_X", "CMx", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Total momentum x-component on all surfaces set with MARKER_MONITORING", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1661  /// DESCRIPTION: Moment around the y-axis
1662  AddHistoryOutput("MOMENT_Y", "CMy", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Total momentum y-component on all surfaces set with MARKER_MONITORING", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1663  /// DESCRIPTION: Moment around the z-axis
1664  AddHistoryOutput("MOMENT_Z", "CMz", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Total momentum z-component on all surfaces set with MARKER_MONITORING", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1665  /// DESCRIPTION: Force in x direction
1666  AddHistoryOutput("FORCE_X", "CFx", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Total force x-component on all surfaces set with MARKER_MONITORING", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1667  /// DESCRIPTION: Force in y direction
1668  AddHistoryOutput("FORCE_Y", "CFy", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Total force y-component on all surfaces set with MARKER_MONITORING", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1669  /// DESCRIPTION: Force in z direction
1670  AddHistoryOutput("FORCE_Z", "CFz", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Total force z-component on all surfaces set with MARKER_MONITORING", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1671  /// DESCRIPTION: Lift-to-drag ratio
1672  AddHistoryOutput("EFFICIENCY", "CEff", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF", "Total lift-to-drag ratio on all surfaces set with MARKER_MONITORING", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1673  /// END_GROUP
1674 
1675  /// BEGIN_GROUP: AERO_COEFF_SURF, DESCRIPTION: Aerodynamic coefficients and forces per surface.
1676  vector<string> Marker_Monitoring;
1677  for (unsigned short iMarker_Monitoring = 0; iMarker_Monitoring < config->GetnMarker_Monitoring(); iMarker_Monitoring++){
1678  Marker_Monitoring.push_back(config->GetMarker_Monitoring_TagBound(iMarker_Monitoring));
1679  }
1680  /// DESCRIPTION: Drag coefficient
1681  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("DRAG_ON_SURFACE", "CD", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Monitoring, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1682  /// DESCRIPTION: Lift coefficient
1683  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("LIFT_ON_SURFACE", "CL", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Monitoring, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1684  /// DESCRIPTION: Sideforce coefficient
1685  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("SIDEFORCE_ON_SURFACE", "CSF", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Monitoring, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1686  /// DESCRIPTION: Moment around the x-axis
1687  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("MOMENT-X_ON_SURFACE", "CMx", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Monitoring, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1688  /// DESCRIPTION: Moment around the y-axis
1689  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("MOMENT-Y_ON_SURFACE", "CMy", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Monitoring, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1690  /// DESCRIPTION: Moment around the z-axis
1691  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("MOMENT-Z_ON_SURFACE", "CMz", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Monitoring, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1692  /// DESCRIPTION: Force in x direction
1693  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("FORCE-X_ON_SURFACE", "CFx", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Monitoring, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1694  /// DESCRIPTION: Force in y direction
1695  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("FORCE-Y_ON_SURFACE", "CFy", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Monitoring, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1696  /// DESCRIPTION: Force in z direction
1697  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("FORCE-Z_ON_SURFACE", "CFz", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Monitoring, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1698  /// DESCRIPTION: Lift-to-drag ratio
1699  AddHistoryOutputPerSurface("EFFICIENCY_ON_SURFACE", "CEff", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AERO_COEFF_SURF", Marker_Monitoring, HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1700  /// END_GROUP
1701 
1702  /// DESCRIPTION: Angle of attack
1703  AddHistoryOutput("AOA", "AoA", ScreenOutputFormat::FIXED, "AOA", "Angle of attack");
1704 
1705  AddHistoryOutput("COMBO", "ComboObj", ScreenOutputFormat::SCIENTIFIC, "COMBO", "Combined obj. function value.", HistoryFieldType::COEFFICIENT);
1706 }

1708 void CFlowOutput::SetAerodynamicCoefficients(const CConfig* config, const CSolver* flow_solver){
1709 
1710  SetHistoryOutputValue("REFERENCE_FORCE", flow_solver->GetAeroCoeffsReferenceForce());
1711  SetHistoryOutputValue("DRAG", flow_solver->GetTotal_CD());
1712  SetHistoryOutputValue("LIFT", flow_solver->GetTotal_CL());
1713  if (nDim == 3)
1714  SetHistoryOutputValue("SIDEFORCE", flow_solver->GetTotal_CSF());
1715  if (nDim == 3){
1716  SetHistoryOutputValue("MOMENT_X", flow_solver->GetTotal_CMx());
1717  SetHistoryOutputValue("MOMENT_Y", flow_solver->GetTotal_CMy());
1718  }
1719  SetHistoryOutputValue("MOMENT_Z", flow_solver->GetTotal_CMz());
1720  SetHistoryOutputValue("FORCE_X", flow_solver->GetTotal_CFx());
1721  SetHistoryOutputValue("FORCE_Y", flow_solver->GetTotal_CFy());
1722  if (nDim == 3)
1723  SetHistoryOutputValue("FORCE_Z", flow_solver->GetTotal_CFz());
1724  SetHistoryOutputValue("EFFICIENCY", flow_solver->GetTotal_CEff());
1725 
1726  for (unsigned short iMarker_Monitoring = 0; iMarker_Monitoring < config->GetnMarker_Monitoring(); iMarker_Monitoring++) {
1727  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("DRAG_ON_SURFACE", flow_solver->GetSurface_CD(iMarker_Monitoring), iMarker_Monitoring);

1733  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("MOMENT-Y_ON_SURFACE", flow_solver->GetSurface_CMy(iMarker_Monitoring), iMarker_Monitoring);
1734  }

1736  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("FORCE-X_ON_SURFACE", flow_solver->GetSurface_CFx(iMarker_Monitoring), iMarker_Monitoring);
1737  SetHistoryOutputPerSurfaceValue("FORCE-Y_ON_SURFACE", flow_solver->GetSurface_CFy(iMarker_Monitoring), iMarker_Monitoring);
